  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>gluten free linguine</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the linguine<strong> </strong>for 8-10 min or until it's cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and reserve a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the skin off your <strong>smoked mackerel fillet[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard</p><p>Tear the <strong>smoked mackerel </strong>into rough pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> dill </strong>and<strong> chives</strong> finely</p><p>Combine the juice of <strong>half </strong>your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span>[4 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>zingy</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Toss the <strong>baby leaf salad </strong>in the <strong>zingy dressing</strong>, then set this aside until serving – this is your<strong> zingy salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>linguine is cooked, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until it starts to sizzle slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>torn smoked mackerel</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained linguine </strong>and<strong> </strong>a few splashes of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then increase the heat to high</p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, stirring until everything is combined and the sauce begins to stick to the pasta</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if the sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze in the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and add <strong>half </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later) with<strong> half</strong> the<strong> chopped dill </strong>and<strong> chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>smoked mackerel gluten free linguine</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-gluten-free-linguine-with-zingy-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked mackerel gluten free linguine</strong> with the<strong> zingy salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>reserved chopped dill </strong>and<strong> chives </strong>all over and then season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
